newsitem.title: THAILAND: Thai interbank rate up, baht steady late.
newsitem.headline: Thai interbank rate up, baht steady late.

text.p: The Thai overnight interbank rate was up to 13.00-13.50 percent in late trade on Tuesday from 12.00 percent earlier and 11.00-12.50 percent late on Monday amid tightening money supply, dealers said.
Dealers said the liquidity was very tight today because banks were maintaining funds for the next reserve requirement and the corporate tax payment had begun to affect the money supply.
The baht was steady at 25.308-25.312 to the dollar in late trade from 25.308-25.311 early as strong demand for baht dampened the dollar's rise, dealers said.

"Dollar buying brought the baht down to as low as 25.322 against the dollar in the afternoon as a result of the U.S.-Iraq crisis," said one currency dealer. "But the tight liquidity and strong demand for baht eventually pushed down the dollar against the baht."
The one-month dollar/baht swap premium rose to 9.75/10.50 satangs late from 8.25/9.25 earlier.
The mid-rate was fixed at 25.32 to the dollar against 25.31 on Monday.
